Author: Alright#0419
Content: I believe the only sensible option for "decentralization" is an algo with a widely available ASIC. Otherwise, once the coin has value, someone will stealth mine with FPGAs defeating the whole purpose of more people having access to mining hardware

Author: Alright#0419
Content: Take for example, 144,5 coins. They all lost their minds when ASICs were announced for 200,9. Now they have FPGAs on their network and no one seems to care? The FPGAs are significantly less widely available than 200,9 ASICs

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: I agree, anything that has a lot of options to mine it is a good thing. Evolution/technological advancements mean people are going to build things that are better and more efficient then what is currently available. So it doesn't really matter what you opt for, eventually it will be superceded

Content: The reason for those prints is mempool transactions propagating out of order. There is nothing to worry about, if you let them all in, then there would be big problems. Once you receive the tx that comes before it, then your node will let it into your mempool.
